    Model specification

Construct parameter vector from list

Source: R/extractParams.R
paramsList2vec.Rd

Given a properly-structered list of parameters, it returns the implied unconstrained parameter vector.

Usage

paramsList2vec(PARAMS_LIST, DIM_EXT, NYB, NYA, N_GRADES, N_EXAMS)

Arguments

PARAMS_LIST

Parameter list. Structure to be documented. See the example.

DIM_EXT

number of external covariates in the competing risk model.

NYB

number of years in the non-graduatable state. Needed for determining how many time-related intercepts in the competing risk model.

NYA

number of years in the graduatable state. Needed for determining how many time-related intercepts in the competing risk model.

N_GRADES

number of grades modelled.

N_EXAMS

number of exams.

Value

It returns the unconstrained parameter vector.

Internal reparameterisations

  • Exam-specific intercepts vector. Decreasing from lower grade to higher. Reparametrised using reparInt(),

  • Latent correlation. Reparameterised via Fisher's transformation.

  • Standard deviations. Reparameterised via exponential transformation.

Examples

seed <- 123

## Setup dimensions
external_covariates <- 3L     # number of external covariates
years_before <- 6L            # number of possible years in the regime without graduation
years_after <- 2L             # number of possible years in the regime with graduation
grades <- 4L                  # number of grades
exams <- 10L                  # number of exams


## Construct the list
params_list <- list()

# Three main blocks
params_list[['CR']] <- list()
params_list[['IRT']] <- list()
params_list[['LAT']] <- list()

# Parameter-blocks related to competing risks
set.seed(seed)
params_list[['CR']][['Dropout']] <- list(
 'Slope_ability' = rnorm(1),
 'Slope_speed' = rnorm(1),
 'Slope_covariates' = rnorm(external_covariates),
 'Intercepts_year' = rnorm(years_before)
)

set.seed(seed+1)
params_list[['CR']][['Transfer']] <- list(
 'Slope_ability' = rnorm(1),
 'Slope_speed' = rnorm(1),
 'Slope_covariates' = rnorm(external_covariates),
 'Intercepts_year' = rnorm(years_before)
)

set.seed(seed+2)
params_list[['CR']][['Graduation']] <- list(
 'Slope_ability' = rnorm(1),
 'Slope_speed' = rnorm(1),
 'Slope_covariates' = rnorm(external_covariates),
 'Intercepts_year' = rnorm(years_after)
)

## Parameter-blocks related to exams IRT-modelling
set.seed(seed+3)
params_list[['IRT']][['Exams_slopes']] <- runif(exams, 0, 5)

set.seed(seed+4)
examsInt <- matrix(0, exams, grades)
for(ex in 1:exams){
examsInt[ex,] <- sort(rnorm(grades, 0, 5), decreasing = TRUE)
}
params_list[['IRT']][['Exams_grades_intercepts']] <- examsInt

set.seed(seed+5)
params_list[['IRT']][['Exams_average_time']] <- rnorm(exams)

set.seed(seed+6)
params_list[['IRT']][['Exams_variability_time']] <- runif(exams)

params_list[['LAT']][['Corr']] <- .6
params_list[['LAT']][['Speed_variability']] <- 1.5

theta <- paramsList2vec(
  PARAMS_LIST = params_list,
  DIM_EXT = external_covariates,
  NYB = years_before,
  NYA = years_after,
  N_GRADES = grades,
  N_EXAMS = exams)
